<p><a name="Nomenclature" id="Nomenclature"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Dalai_Lama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Nomenclature">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Nomenclature</span></h2>
<p>"Dalai" means "Ocean" in <a href="/wiki/Mongolian_language" title="Mongolian language">Mongolian</a>, and is a translation of the Tibetan name "Gyatso," while "<a href="/wiki/Lama" title="Lama">Lama</a>" is the Tibetan equivalent of the <a href="/wiki/Sanskrit" title="Sanskrit">Sanskrit</a> word "<a href="/wiki/Guru" title="Guru">guru</a>," and is commonly translated to mean "spiritual teacher."<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> Putting the terms together, the full title is "Ocean Teacher" meaning a teacher who is spiritually as deep as the ocean.</p>
<p><a name="History" id="History"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Dalai_Lama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: History">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">History</span></h2>
<table class="infobox" cellpadding="3" style="clear: right; width: 27em; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 83%; line-height: 1.2em">
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: middle; width: 65px">
<div class="center">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Zhongwen.svg" class="image" title="Zhongwen.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Zhongwen.svg/65px-Zhongwen.svg.png" width="65" height="33" border="0" /></a></div>
</div>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: middle"><b>This article contains <a href="/wiki/Chinese_language" title="Chinese language">Chinese</a> text.</b> Without proper <a href="/wiki/Help:Multilingual_support_(East_Asian)" title="Help:Multilingual support (East Asian)">rendering support</a>, you may see <a href="/wiki/Mojibake" title="Mojibake">question marks, boxes, or other symbols</a> instead of <a href="/wiki/Chinese_character" title="Chinese character">Chinese characters</a>.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<table class="infobox" cellpadding="3" style="clear: right; width: 27em; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 83%; line-height: 1.2em">
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: middle; width: 65px">
<div class="center">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Example.of.complex.text.rendering.svg" class="image" title="Example.of.complex.text.rendering.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Example.of.complex.text.rendering.svg/65px-Example.of.complex.text.rendering.svg.png" width="65" height="31" border="0" /></a></div>
</div>
